cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI - The paper focuses on leveraging AI-enabled Multi-Agent Systems for decision making and distributed learning capabilities at the device level. 
2. cs.DC - The paper discusses the use of blockchain as an economic transactional layer and governance layer between the devices in the network, which falls under the domain of distributed computing. 
3. cs.CY - The paper discusses the security and privacy aspects of using blockchain for real-time smart contracts, which falls under the domain of cybersecurity. 
4. cs.CR - The paper discusses the use of blockchain for securing the privacy of the participants, which falls under the domain of cryptography. 
5. cs.NI - The paper discusses the monetization of real-time data coming from various IoT devices, which falls under the domain of networked systems and communication.
